radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis, dilated and thickened appendix measuring 1 cm with adjacent fat stranding and thickening of the lateral conal fascia. No pleural effusion, pneumothorax, or free air/fluid. Normal liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, and small bowel. Mildly prominent adjacent lymph nodes. No suspicious osseous lesions.
